                <fr:title text="properties of isomorphism">properties of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00L0.xml" title="isomorphic sets" addr="jms-00L0" type="local">isomorphism</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>The concept of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00L0.xml" title="isomorphic sets" addr="jms-00L0" type="local">isomorphism</fr:link> between two sets satisfies laws like those of an <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00L4.xml" title="equivalence relation" addr="jms-00L4" type="local">equivalence relation</fr:link>. In particular:</html:p>
                <html:ol><html:li>reflexivity: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\cong  A]]></fr:tex>;</html:li>
 <html:li>transitivity: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\cong  B \land  B \cong  C \implies  A \cong  C]]></fr:tex>;</html:li>
 <html:li>symmetry: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\cong  B \implies  B\cong  A]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol>
              </fr:mainmatter>
