              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>For all sets <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A,B,X,Y]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\cong  X \land  B\cong  Y\implies  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}\cong  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (X,Y\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>25</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>jms-00LK/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00LK/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="invariance under isomorphism › forest://jonmsterling/jms-00LK/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00LK.xml" title="invariance under isomorphism" addr="jms-00LK" type="local">invariance under isomorphism</fr:link> › jms-00LK/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>Fix <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KR.xml" title="bijection" addr="jms-00KR" type="local">bijections</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B \to  Y]]></fr:tex>. We will define a bijection <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H\colon  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}\to  \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (X,Y\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>

 <html:p>Given <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } B]]></fr:tex>, we define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}\colon  X\mathbin {\nrightarrow } Y]]></fr:tex> to be the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IN.xml" title="relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">relational composite</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  R\circ  f^{-1}]]></fr:tex>. The inverse mapping <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H^{-1}\colon \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (X,Y\right )\mathclose {}}\to \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is defined to take <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S\colon  X\mathbin {\nrightarrow } Y]]></fr:tex> to the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IN.xml" title="relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">relational composite</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g^{-1} \circ  S\circ  f]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>

 <html:p>Next, we check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H^{-1}]]></fr:tex> is simulatneously a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KS.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="jms-00KS" type="local">retraction</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KS.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="jms-00KS" type="local">section</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   H^{-1}{\mathopen {}\left (H{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}} &= g^{-1}\circ  H{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}\circ  f\\
